# 23. Co wpisać do README przy najbliższej okazji

Przy najbliższej czystej okazji trzeba dodać krótką sekcję zasad:

```txt
Target Product Architecture Decisions

- Polutek.pl is a single-creator VOD/patron platform, not a marketplace or multi-creator SaaS.
- Cloudflare Stream is the target video delivery provider.
- Video access tiers are PUBLIC, LOGGED_IN, and PATRON.
- Comment sections are visible to everyone.
- Commenting on PUBLIC and LOGGED_IN videos requires login.
- Commenting on PATRON videos requires active patron access or admin role.
- Subscription means mailing/follow consent, not patron access.
- Patron access is granted only through PatronGrant.
- Stripe never directly grants patron status.
- Eligible payments, admin actions, and referral rewards may create PatronGrants through explicit use-cases.
- Clerk metadata and User.isPatron are read/cache/read-model only, not source of truth.
- Access decisions must go through access/patron modules, not route-local checks.
```

Nie oznaczać jeszcze tych rzeczy jako wykonanych, jeśli nie są wykonane. To są target decisions / planned architecture.

